{{en-verb}}

# (usually with ''on'') To repeatedly [[mention]] a subject.
#: ''Why do you '''harp on''' about a single small mistake?''
# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To [[play]] on (a harp or similar instrument).
# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To play (a tune) on the harp.
# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To develop or give expression to by skill and art; to sound forth as from a harp; to hit upon.
#: ''Thou '''harped''' my fear aright.'' &mdash; Shakespeare.

